## Tooling Guidance by Stack

- Microsoft-centric: Copilot across Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, Teams, Power Automate, AI Builder, and Copilot Studio agents covers most admin/document workflows with enterprise governance.[^3][^6][^11][^28][^4]
- Google-centric: Gemini/Bard integrates with Docs, Gmail, Calendar, Drive; useful for comms, scheduling, and collaboration.[^19][^40][^9][^41][^7]
- Content/marketing: Jasper for brand consistency, workflows, SEO-ready copy, and brief-to-campaign automation.[^27][^10][^8]
- Research-heavy and reasoning: Claude 3.5 Sonnet excels at long-context analysis, compliance alignment, and policy/RFP synthesis.[^2][^18]
- Document AI/IDP: Google Document AI or Microsoft AI Builder for OCR, forms, and structured extraction.[^11][^31]
- Embedded reporting: Jaspersoft for pixel-perfect and embedded BI; modern automated reporting stacks and Whatagraph/Coupler for marketing analytics.[^13][^5][^12]

Implementation tip: Start with a narrow, high-volume use case (e.g., meeting minutes, expense extraction, status reporting), wire it into existing systems, then expand to adjacent workflows with clear success metrics and human oversight for sensitive outputs.[^42][^43][^29][^3][^4]

